    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">King Ferdinand I to Pál Várday and Miklós Oláh (Wiener Neustadt,
                    19 September 1548)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>Although the dispute between Thomas Kobilsky and his enemy has been
                            postponed to the next Bratislava assembly, he is certain that Oláh and
                            Várday have not forgotten about him. Since Kobilsky requested to be let
                            out on bail so that he can better prepare for clearing his name, King
                            Ferdinand I graciously allowed to set him free under these conditions.
                            He asks Várday and Oláh to help him find suitable guarantors, and as
                            soon as they have them, Kobilsky will be released from his shackles.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Ferdinandus etc. Reverendissime in Christo Pater ac Venerabilis, Devoti
                    Fideles nobis Dilecti!</p>
                <p>Quamquam nos causam et controversiam illam inter <persName>Thomam
                        Kobilsky</persName>,<note type="critic">We do not know him more
                        closely.</note> qui captivus in custodia nostra detinetur, et adversarium
                    suum existentem ad conventum generalem <placeName>Posonii</placeName> propediem
                        congregandum<note type="critic">16 October, 1548, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Mikó</hi> 2017, 69–73.</note> reieceramus ac distuleramus, sicuti
                    Devotionem et Fidelitatem Vestram recenti adhuc memoria tenere non ambigimus,
                    tamen quoniam <del corresp="scriba">denuo</del> praefatus captivus
                        <persName>Thomas</persName> nobis denuo humillime supplicavit, quatenus eum
                        <del corresp="scriba">non obstante priori nostro decreto</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">sub legitima et sufficienti cautione
                        fideiussoria</add> gratiose liberum <add corresp="scriba" type="insert"
                        >dimittimere</add> dignaremur, ut eo facilius se ad purgationem
                    excusationemque suam necessariis et opportunis rationibus ac fulcimentis munire
                    et instruere valeat, offerens se ante sui eliberationem <del corresp="scriba"
                        >sufficientissimum quoque vadimonium praestare atque ad terminum praefixum
                        sistere vel in vincula redire velle</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr"
                        >huiusmodi fideiussoriae cautionem ac vadimonium pressiturum</add>. Nos
                    idcirco attenta humili petitione dicti captivi, nec non <del corresp="scriba"
                        >obstante</del> habita ratione praeclarissimae gravissimaeque intercessionis
                    pro ipso apud nos <del corresp="scriba">factae summa cum autoritate</del> factae
                    clementer annuimus et consensimus praefatum <persName>Thomam</persName>
                    <del corresp="scriba">liber</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">sub</add>
                    praedicta conditione ab ipso oblata e custodia et captivitate liberum dimitti.
                    Atque propterea etiam iussimus curavimusque quamprimum sufficientes <add
                        corresp="scriba" type="insert">et idoneae</add> personae coram Fidelitate
                    Vestra comparuerint, <del corresp="scriba">vadimoniam praestiterint
                        promiserintque quod ipsum Thomam iterum Posonium ad conventum generalem
                        provenire futurum coram nobis sistere, vel ipsimet sive loco stare
                        velint</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">quae legitimam ac sufficientem
                        cautionem <del corresp="scriba">iure iurando ut moris est</del>
                        praestiterint</add>, prout ipse <del corresp="scriba">quoque</del>
                    <persName>Thomas</persName> se effecturum offert ac <milestone unit="pb"/>pollicetur, quod captivorum custos seu provosius noster saepedictum
                        <persName>Thomam</persName> statim liberum e vinculis et custodia dimittat.
                    De qua sane re Fidelitatem Vestram, ut eius notitiam haberet, certiorem reddere
                    voluimus.</p>
                <p>Datum in <placeName>Nova Civitate</placeName> 19. Septembris 1548.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>Probably on the outer side:</head>
                <p>Strigoniensi et Zagrabiensi.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
